title: Longclaw
description:
by Writerwhowrites

Jon left four years ago, the scandal of her betrothed’s death and her unborn child raised many questions. Arya doesn’t believe what they say about her cousin.

“He dishonored the girl. She was with child, and when she heard that the prince had left, with no care for her or the babe he’d sired on her, she throw herself into the sea.”

Lord Forrester had come to Winterfell to demand a duel with Jon. “How dare he dishonor my precious daughter and then leave her as if she was nothing but a tavern wench?” he’d shouted for everyone to hear.

Father, Rodrik, Jon, Robb, Alyssa and probably Mother… (Those are the only ones who know the whole truth.) But Alyssa had killed herself a moon later, and Jon was gone, and father wouldn’t speak, and now Rodrik was also dead.

summary: Thanks for answering ask. But do you think jon would ever be with anyone who basically brought down and led to the death of his...
question: Thanks for answering ask. But do you think jon would ever be with anyone who basically brought down and led to the death of his family ? I think the only way I could see this happening if it was forced or he was her prisoner.
answer:
You’re welcome!

I understand where you’re coming from, I see why you would have a hard time imagining show!Jon going along with this, but this is how I see it:

If Jon thought it was really necessary to protect his family and his home, and/or to save the world, I think he would do it.

I guess it depends on whether he’s got other people to help him make that choice. If he has his family around him, and he’s willing to listen to them, he might decide to do something else, but if he’s reluctant about accepting help, I can see him doing it.

If he’s desperate enough, he could become really stubborn about it, refusing to change his mind and becoming blind to other possible options.

This would definitely be true if he becomes a prisoner again, or if he has to make this decision under any other kind of duress.

I think people are willing to push their limits when times are desperate, and Jon will probably know some of his darkest moments during season 8.

I’ll add again that I think it’s extremely unlikely we’ll see this happening in season 8, but I wouldn’t say it’s impossible.

Thank you for the question!

body:
It’s very special moment that Jon was there When Jorah arrived.

First reason.

It was very special that Dany spoke with Dothraki language. Jon couldn’t understand who is ser Joras. Especialy who is Jorah for Dany. How he looked at Jorah. With confuse eyes and little angry

And Dany explane to him “he is friend”

We can see his jealous face and confuse moment right now.

Second reason

When Dany hugged with Jorah. Jon looked at queen with confuse face again.

Why?

It’s not normal situation in Westeros when High Born people (especially Royal family) has such an gentle relationship with advisors or servants. Jon rememberers proud Lannisters and Baratheons when they arrived first season in Winterfel.

He remembers Landy Stark who always descriptions that Her children were trueborns and Jon was only Bastard.

It’s normal that Jon is confuse about her action. She is so loyal, gentle and sweet.probably he finally understands why her people loves her so much.

He realised that she isn’t like everyone else

summary: Ew Cersei and Jon sex scene is a joke right?
question: Ew Cersei and Jon sex scene is a joke right?
answer:
Who knows, anon?

Cersei wanted to bang both of Jon’s dads and Jon has already fucked one Southron queen. And to be honest, it’s a union they could both benefit from under the right circumstances, so… ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

In all seriousness, I think Jon and Cersei is an interesting crack ship with a couple of possible dynamics that would be fun to explore in fanfic, and I could even see some merit in ~something minor~ being alluded to or implied in canon, but I don’t believe it’s going to happen.

As to D&D’s comment about “a sexy scene”, that could literally be anything, or even nothing at all. Definitely not worth losing a night of sleep over, anon!
